book.name: Weblinks - How to Guide
book.intro:
Using Web Links ...

Web-based resources can greatly assist students undertaking research or gaining background information, however, allowing uncontrolled access to the web by asking "see what you can find about John Doe's Invention" often leads to a lot of unproductive web browsing, and can be very distracting.Â 

To focus student activity within the ATEP courses, you will see a lot of Web Page links ...

Clicking on the Link will generally open a new browser tab, and take students to the desired information ...

Once the student has completed their research, they should close the browser tab by clicking on the CLOSE TAB indicator ...
